  "text": "Crispening is a complex form of simultaneous contrast. It is the increase in perceived magnitude of color differences between two samples (in lightness or chromaticity) when the background to the samples is similar in lightness or chromaticity to the samples [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
